Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in large skillet over medium heat. Stir in mushrooms, carrots and onion and cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until tender. Add remaining ingredients except hazelnuts. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until rice is tender. Meanwhile, melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in small skillet over medium heat. Cook hazelnuts in butter, stirring constantly, or until brown and fragrant. Remove from skillet. Just before serving, stir in hazelnuts. Season with salt and pepper.